<title>CZECH REPUBLIC: Czech bank CZK 1.886 bln 96 net profit-CAS.</title>
<headline>Czech bank CZK 1.886 bln 96 net profit-CAS.</headline>
<dateline>PRAGUE 1997-03-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Audited results, calculated according to Czech accounting standards (CAS) for year ending December 31, 1996:</p>
<p>(in billions of crowns)</p>
<p> Net profit		1.886    vs    0.263</p>
<p> Net interest income  13.389    vs   13.645</p>
<p> Operating costs	11.104    vs   10.271</p>
<p>Balance sheet</p>
<p>  total		  359.019    vs  367.848</p>
<p> Primary deposits    294.797    vs  294.660</p>
<p> Creation of reserves  4.663    vs    7.104</p>
<p>Classified loans as a percentage</p>
<p>  of loan portfolio    24.7 pct  vs   n/a</p>
<p> Provision coverage   53.52 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p>Gross loan provision</p>
<p>  coverage		66.05 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p> Net interest margin   4.84 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p> Cost income ration   62.08 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p> Return on assets	0.54 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p> Return on equity	9.74 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p>Capital adequacy</p>
<p>  ratio		    8.86 pct vs   n/a</p>
<p> Earnings per share   24.82 crowns</p>
<p>Note. Full company name is Ceska Sporitelna a.s., the country's largest savings bank. Provision coverage is against non-standard doubtful and lost loans. Classified loans are calculated according the Czech National Bank's methodology.</p>
<p>Sporitelna added in a statement that according to its auditor, KPMG, reserves fully covered risky loans.</p>
<p>-- Prague Newsroom, 420-2-2423-0003</p>
